#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=ANNABEL LEE .
#Text=IT was many and many a year ago , In a kingdom by the sea , That a maiden there lived whom you may know By the name of ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=And this maiden she lived with no other thought Than to love and be loved by me .
#Text=I was a child and she was a child , In this kingdom by the sea :
#Text=But we loved with a love that was more than love —
#Text=I and my ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=With a love that the winged seraphs of heaven Coveted her and me .
#Text=And this was the reason that , long ago , In this kingdom by the sea , A wind blew out of a cloud , chilling My beautiful ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=So that her highborn kinsman came And bore her away from me , To shut her up in a sepulchre In this kingdom by the sea .
#Text=The angels , not half so happy in heaven , Went envying her and me —
#Text=Yes ! — that was the reason ( as all men know , In this kingdom by the sea ) That the wind came out of the cloud by night , Chilling and killing my ANNABEL LEE .
#Text=But our love it was stronger by far than the love Of those who were older than we —
#Text=Of many far wiser than we —
#Text=And neither the angels in heaven above , Nor the demons down under the sea , Can ever dissever my soul from the soul Of the beautiful ANNABEL LEE :
#Text=For the moon never beams , without bringing me dreams Of the beautiful ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=And the stars never rise , but I feel the bright eyes Of the beautiful ANNABEL LEE ;
#Text=And so , all the night - tide , I lie down by the side Of my darling — my darling — my life and my bride , In the sepulchre there by the sea , In her tomb by the sounding sea .
